title: MQM’s Muhammad Dilawar wins PS-108 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Mutahidda Quomi Movement’s (MQM) Muhammad Dilawar has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-108, Karachi South-III, by securing 20,014 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Murad Sheikh, who bagged 16,850 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 30.31 %.
